These notifications are merely because the given URIs -- of schemes 'file:',
'clsid:', and 'mailto:' -- are unschedulable. No workQueue for lining them up
with other related URIs is defined... but that's OK, because they shouldn't be
fetched in any case.

You would still get these whether the SWF extractor is present or not.

I believe these notifications to be harmless, but there's an existing bug
report to divert such unschedulable URI types earlier. See:

  [ 963970 ] unfetchable URI schemes should never be queued
  http://sourceforge.net/tracker/index.php?func=detail&aid=963970&group_id=73833&atid=539099

- Gordon @ IA
